### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

animations

### Description

Let's consider a simple scenario where we use the Angular @fadeInOnEnter animation to smoothly fade in a target element when it gets created:

```html
<div @fadeInOnEnter>
    Some content
</div>
```

What happens when using SSR (Server-Side Rendering) in this scenario?

1. The browser receives a pre-rendered page where this element is already rendered in its final state (i.e., it is completely visible).
2. The user immediately sees the element.
3. The hydration process completes.
4. The animated element disappears and the animation starts playing.

The result looks really bad because all animated elements flicker, making Angular enter animations ineffective when using SSR.

### Proposed solution

To avoid this flickering, we need kind of **SSRAnimationsModule** on the server side. This animation module must apply styles that reflect the initial state of the animated element rather than its final state (in our scenario, it should be transparent).

In this case, the user will initially see no element. After a short delay, once the hydration process is completed, the element will be animated as desired, avoiding the flickering issue.

### Alternatives considered

1. Workarounds look really weird and require playing with animation delays and other adjustments.
2. It is simpler to implement the desired behavior using native CSS animations:

our css file with desired animation keyframes:
```css

.fade-in {
  animation: fadeIn 1s ease-in-out;
}

@keyframes fadeIn {
  0% {
    opacity: 0;
  }

  to {
    opacity: 1;
  }
}

```
our component html file:
```html

<div class="fade-in" appPauseAnimationOnServer>
</div>


```
our directive which pauses animation on a server and starts playing it once hydration process is completed:

```ts
@Directive({
  selector: '[appPauseAnimationsOnServer]',
  standalone: true
})
export class PauseAnimationsOnServerDirective implements OnInit {

  constructor(private el: ElementRef<HTMLElement>,
              @Inject(PLATFORM_ID) private platformId: Object) {

  }

  ngOnInit(): void {
    if (isPlatformServer(this.platformId)) {
      this.el.nativeElement.style.animationPlayState = 'paused';
    } else {
      this.el.nativeElement.style.animationPlayState = 'running';
    }
  }

}
```

